This paper discusses the security of cloud applications, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also proposes an approach inspired by biological immune systems, which involves adapting and actively attacking potential intruders, which could fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE) or distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also evaluates popular cloud service infrastructures, which could fall under the categories of systems and infrastructure (cs.SI) or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
